Czym jest WASM?

  • Nowy rodzaj kodu

    • main.ts

    
						export function add (x: i32, y: i32): i32 {
							return (x + y) * y;
						}

    main.js

    
						WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming(fetch("main.wasm"))
							.then(result => {
								const exports = result.instance.exports;
								document.getElementById("container")
									.textContent = `Result: ${exports.add(19, 2)}`; // Result: 42
							});

    Czym jest WASM?

    main.wasm

    
						(module
							(type $t0 (func (param i32 i32) (result i32)))
							(func $add (export "add") (type $t0) (param $p0 i32) (param $p1 i32) (result i32)
								get_local $p1
								get_local $p0
								get_local $p1
								i32.add
								i32.mul)
							(memory $memory (export "memory") 0))

    Uycie WASM

    Blazor

  • Wykorzystanie natywnych aplikacji
  • Wsparcie AOT
  • Wiksze pliki, ale szybsze dziaanie

    • Blazor

    3DDisplay.razor

    
						@page "/3d-display"
						...
						
						...
						@code {
							[DllImport("3dmodule")]
    						static extern void get3D(string itemName, buffer);

							[Parameter] public string Value { get; set; } = string.Empty;

							protected override void OnParametersSet()
							{
								get3D(Value, buffer);
							}

							protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
        						=> await JS.InvokeVoidAsync("bufferToCanvas", canvasElem, buffer);
						}

    Program.cs

    
						builder.RootComponents.RegisterAsCustomElement<3D>("3d-display");

    main.js

    
						<3d-display value="headphones" />
